Delivery partners and people using delivery “BEWARE”. This location will make you wait for orders while customers that come in after you get taken care of 1st. Potbelly’s restaurant locations are notorious for doing this to delivery partners.

I love Potbelly and was excited to move so close to one of the locations! However, I have consistently had to wait 15-20 minutes after my mobile order ETA. They ask everyone there 2-4 times what their name is so they can get the order ready instead of it being ready on the given arrival time. I have been to Potbelly locations that are run like well oiled machines so it’s very disappointing to consistently have bad service here.

Many negative reviews appear to be people frustrated with the third-party delivery services, and not this store. That service is responsible for handling the food from the store's counter to your doorstep, when quality is impossible for this store to control. The lady crying about her smoothie is hilarious. The delivery driver probably had a few swigs before giving it to you then sealed it back up. That review reminds me of the video of the fat lady at the Taco Bell counter demanding more cheese on her nachos. Anyways.. love the food and smoothies!

Just ordered off Uber Eats. The delivery was great. But when I got my meal, everything was there, though the smoothie I ordered, which was in the sealed bag, was only half full. Like I can't even make this up, only half of the short smoothie cup was filled. HALF. Which is utterly ridiculous. Who makes a smoothie order, pours it in the cup and doesn't notice that they only made enough to fill up half the cup and then has the nerve to send it on it's way to be delivered?
My food was made correctly and the staff was nice but the food just didn't taste that good. Not sure why but will probably go somewhere else in the future.

Ordered via Grubhub and the delivery took nearly two hours. When I contacted grubhub, support contacted the restaurant and Potbelly blamed the significant delay on TRAFFIC, despite being less than 1 mile away. When my order finally arrived, the driver handed me a dripping wet bag and explained my drink had spilled. He kept a fountain drink I didn’t order inside the bag, as it was spilling over everything. But don’t worry- it was completely the wrong order and clearly was someone else’s order. I did not order a fountain drink and have no idea why I am now mopping up someone else’s sticky sprite off my floor. Everything had to be thrown away, as it was drenched in sprite and freezing cold, but no worries because it wasn’t even my order. Waited two hours to mop my floor, and got to pay $39 for it. 0/5.

Customer service was horrible. No one smiled even once. No one greeted us as we came. After standing at the order end of the line for awhile, i started to wonder if i was on the wrong side. No one was helping me. I walked to cashier side and asked if i orser on that side. She just glared at me and pointed to the other end. When she finally came over, she didnt say anything about making me wait. Moving on, as i ordered, i asked a couple of questions about the toppings. Like if they could do onions on half. She literally didnt even say anything to me. I was met with silence for each question. I even looked over at the customer next to me in a sort of "is this happening?!" way. I was not alone in my disbelief. After finally getting our food we went and sat outside. The woman came and kicked us out of our chairs after 10 minutes saying they had to close. They had a ton of people inside still and it was 15 minutes til close. I got up and tries to pack away my food as quickly as possible. Unfortunately that wasnt quick enough for her. She yanked a chair, to stack it away. Without any care for the dog that was attached by a leash to it. She yanked my friends sleeping puppy to its feet. After i intervened and asked her to take ot down a notch. She moved to grab my food and throw it away. I had to tale it out of her hands. She looked at me and said, "oh, is that not trash?" It CLEARLY wasnt. I would never go back to this establishment.
